writeToParcel(android.os.Parcel, int).FullName: public void writeToParcel (Parcel out, int flags)

Parameters: The Android package name of an Android application to be installed or launched to discover and communicate with the advertised service (e.g. com.example.myapp).

getIdentifier().Description: Retrieves the identifier string for this application (e.g. com.example.mygame).

ClassDesc: An identifier for an application; the value of the identifier should be the package name for an Android application to be installed or launched to discover and communicate with the advertised service (e.g. com.example.myapp). Google applications may use this data to prompt the user to install the application.
